      "description": "This E46 M3 is a superlative example of BMW M-Division engineering. At its heart lies the S54B32 inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure dual-VANOS system, delivering a seamless 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock for optimal torque distribution. The chassis is impeccably preserved with documented subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive rod bearing service already performed. Suspension bushings and dampers remain within factory tolerances, ensuring the precise turn-in and lateral stability this platform is renowned for. An unmolested, showroom-quality specimen for the discerning collector.",
